13/06/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The interior ministry and customs agency launched a two-day international drug traffic prevention forum Tuesday (13 June), in collaboration with the Council of Europe. Some 100 participants from 34 countries are attending the event. According to Deputy Interior Minister Boyko Kotzev, the fight against illegal drug trafficking must be waged through consolidated efforts by all European countries. Customs chief Asen Asenov said Bulgaria has thwarted more than 500 cases of drug trafficking over the last five years at Bulgarian airports, seizing more than 26 tonnes of drugs, mainly cocaine. (Dnevnik, 24 chasa, BTA - 12/06/06)
